<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Locally found exclusively from deeper soft sediment habitats of the island. Depth 14-25 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Misidentified by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" author="Chavanich, S" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B49" refString="Chavanich, S, Viyakarn, V, Sanpanich, K, Harris, L, 2013. Diversity and occurrence of nudibranchs in Thailand. Marine Biodiversity 43: 31 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" title="Diversity and occurrence of nudibranchs in Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" volume="43" year="2013">Chavanich et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kanga" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="kanga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">H. kanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a recorded distribution in both Andaman Sea and Gulf coasts of Thailand.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rudman" authorityYear="1977" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Hypselodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hypselodoris kanga" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kanga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Hypselodoris kanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears blueish purple lines across its dorsum which are absent in this species, instead replaced by deep blue, almost black spots. These are more abundant towards the margin where they diffuse outwards turning into blue streaks closer to the edge. Given the historic confusion surrounding 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kanga" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="kanga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">H. kanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zly048" author="Epstein, HE" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="116 - 189" refId="B73" refString="Epstein, HE, Hallas, JM, Johnson, RF, Lopez, A, Gosliner, TM, 2018. Reading between the lines: revealing cryptic species diversity and colour patterns in Hypselodoris nudibranchs (Mollusca: Heterobranchia: Chromodorididae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 1: 116 - 189, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zly048" title="Reading between the lines: revealing cryptic species diversity and colour patterns in Hypselodoris nudibranchs (Mollusca: Heterobranchia: Chromodorididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zly048" volume="1" year="2018">Epstein et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), this difference in colouration merits the need for a closer investigation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
